               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>My council is instructed, my lord, in my defence.</p>
               <p>Council for the Prisoner to young Mr. Alexander. Do you know of any notes the prisoner had given your father?</p>
               <p>Alexander. No.</p>
               <p>Q. Not a note payable in two months?</p>
               <p>Alexander. No.</p>
               <p>Q. to the elder Mr. Alexander. You remember, I believe, he gave you a note payable in two months?</p>
               <p>Alexander. Yes; after he was gone from me.</p>
